Package: libretro-bsnes-accuracy
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: retroarch | libretro-frontend, ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Libretro wrapper for bsnes accuracy profile
 This wrapper makes bsnes accuracy profile API compatible with libretro, thus
 allowing its use with libretro frontends, such as RetroArch.
 .
 bsnes focuses on accuracy of SNES hardware emulation and clean code above all
 else. It never uses speed or compatibility hacks. As a result, the minimum
 system requirements are higher than with other emulators.
 .
 This package comes with the bsnes accuracy profile, which runs 100% of SNES
 games, with perfect emulation of the console. It requires high CPU usage.

Package: libretro-bsnes-balanced
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: retroarch | libretro-frontend, ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Libretro wrapper for bsnes balanced profile
 This wrapper makes bsnes balanced profile API compatible with libretro, thus
 allowing its use with libretro frontends, such as RetroArch.
 .
 bsnes focuses on accuracy of SNES hardware emulation and clean code above all
 else. It never uses speed or compatibility hacks. As a result, the minimum
 system requirements are higher than with other emulators.
 .
 This package comes with the bsnes balanced profile, which tries to keep a good
 balance between accuracy and performance. It runs almost all SNES games.

Package: libretro-bsnes-performance
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: retroarch | libretro-frontend, ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Libretro wrapper for bsnes performance profile
 This wrapper makes bsnes performance profile API compatible with libretro, thus
 allowing its use with libretro frontends, such as RetroArch.
 .
 bsnes focuses on accuracy of SNES hardware emulation and clean code above all
 else. It never uses speed or compatibility hacks. As a result, the minimum
 system requirements are higher than with other emulators.
 .
 This package comes with the bsnes performance profile, which provides faster
 emulation at the cost of reduced accuracy, including problems with some games.
